<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-58-0726 </DOCNO><TEXT>The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) has established a technologyresearch, demonstration, and evaluation program to promote the use ofinnovative technologies for the treatment and destruction of hazardous-wastematerials. In response to the Superfund Amendments and ReauthorizationAct of 1986 (SARA), the Office of Research and Development (ORD) andOSWER have established the Superfund Innovative Technology Evaluation(SITE) program to accelerate the development and use of alternative technologiesat Superfund sites. The SITE program will provide assurance on performancedata and cost information on those technologies.</TEXT></DOC>